On World Autism Awareness Day, President Joe Biden acknowledges the contributions of people with autism to society while highlighting the challenges they face. He emphasizes the need for funding research to better understand autism and improve the quality of life for individuals and their families. The government has taken initiatives to detect autism early, fund research networks, and provide services and support for independent living. Efforts are also being made to protect the rights of people with disabilities, reduce disparities in access to healthcare and education, and address the unique disruptions caused by the COVID-19 pandemic. President Biden calls for increased awareness, understanding, and inclusive communities to support people with autism.